:INFO
Design and Transfer
Keep your first design bold and simple: thick lines and solid shapes print more reliably \
than fine detail. Draw your design on paper, then transfer it to the lino block by \
tracing it face-down with a pencil and rubbing the back, or by using graphite

:PATH
Carve the Block
Work with a set of linocut gouges.
|
:INFO
Carve the Block
Work with a set of linocut gouges. V-gouges cut fine lines and outlines; U-gouges remove \
large background areas quickly. Always cut away from your hands and body. The lino will \
be easier to carve if you warm it slightly with a heat pad or by leaving it

